Global Rubber-Gelatin Lifters Market Insights
Rubber-Gelatin Lifters Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.0 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Rubber-Gelatin Lifters Market Overview
The global rubber-gelatin lifters market is valued at approximately USD 1.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a steady compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.1% from 2024 to 2032. This growth can be attributed to the increasing demand for durable and high-performance lifters across various industries, including manufacturing, mining, and automotive sectors. These lifters, made from a combination of rubber and gelatin, are widely used in handling sensitive materials and machinery due to their superior shock absorption and resistance to wear and tear. Rising industrial automation and the need for robust lifting equipment have been key contributors to the market's expansion.

